description:
The rooftops of Venice, Italy. This photograph was taken from the top of the Campanile di San Marco, looking north over the city. Despite the apparent multitude of residential units, Venice is a city in decline. Jobs outside of the tourism industry are rare, and Venitians are increasingly leaving the island city for the mainland and better opportunities. This exodus has been heavily accelerated by the COVID-19 pandemic and the associated drop-off in incoming tourists.

Colour photograph. 6353 × 4235 JPEG.
